-- Shanghai to Build 400 Electric Car Charging Stations, Business News Says
-- Bloomberg News
-- 2010-06-30T00:07:20Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-30/shanghai-to-build-400-electric-car-charging-stations-business-news-says.html

          
          
             The Shanghai government will build
400 charging stations for electric vehicles this year, China
Business News said, citing Liu Jianhua, an official in charge of
promoting alternative-energy vehicles in the city.  
 The city government will add SAIC Motor Corp.â€™s hybrid
vehicles, Roewe 750, to its purchase list in a bid to raise
awareness of alternative-energy vehicles, the newspaper said.
SAIC will begin selling Roewe 750 at the end of this year, it
said.  
          
          


  


        